                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/392: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        American Representatives on the Organizing Committee for the International
                        Monetary and Economic Conference (<persName corresp="#p_DNH1" type="to"
                            >Davis</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SFM1"
                        >Sackett</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 9, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. For <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>. Your 60, December 8, 10
                    p.m. The American representatives will be present at the next meeting of the
                    Preparatory Commission on January 9. The Department accepts your judgment that
                    it would be unwise to try to postpone this date now. The experts will have to
                    carry through as best they can, guarding at a later time against the convocation
                    of the Conference itself until the chances of success are clear.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
